            <h3>1. Desktop Survey & Species Selection</h3>
            <div style="background:#e3f1e3; border-radius:2rem; padding:2rem;">
                <h4>Florabank Guidelines: Essential Planning Steps</h4>
                <ul style="margin-left:2rem;">
                    <li><strong>Desktop survey:</strong> AVH, Atlas of Living Australia, regional vegetation guides, local council databases</li>
                    <li><strong>Species list refinement:</strong> consider seed storage behaviour (orthodox/recalcitrant), collection difficulty, quantity needed</li>
                    <li><strong>Phenology research:</strong> flowering and fruiting periods from herbarium records, previous collections (Australian Seed Bank Partnership)</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <h3>2. Work Plan Components (Detailed)</h3>
            <div class="checklist-super">
                <h4><i class="fas fa-check-double"></i> Mandatory Work Plan Elements</h4>
                <div class="checklist-grid">
                    <div class="checklist-item"><input type="checkbox"> <strong>Species required:</strong> botanical name, common name, target quantity, fruit type (A/B/C)</div>
                    <div class="checklist-item"><input type="checkbox"> <strong>Location details:</strong> property name, reserve, GPS coordinates (GDA2020), access notes</div>
                    <div class="checklist-item"><input type="checkbox"> <strong>Timing:</strong> preferred collection window, backup dates, flowering status check</div>
                    <div class="checklist-item"><input type="checkbox"> <strong>Permits:</strong> permit numbers attached, landholder permission letter, Indigenous consultation</div>
                    <div class="checklist-item"><input type="checkbox"> <strong>Personnel:</strong> collector names, supervisor contact, emergency contacts (3 people)</div>
                    <div class="checklist-item"><input type="checkbox"> <strong>Equipment list:</strong> collection tools, cleaning gear, PPE, vehicles</div>
                    <div class="checklist-item"><input type="checkbox"> <strong>Transport & logistics:</strong> cool storage, delivery arrangements to nursery/seed bank</div>
                    <div class="checklist-item"><input type="checkbox"> <strong>Risk assessment:</strong> WHS and environmental hazards signed off</div>
                    <div class="checklist-item"><input type="checkbox"> <strong>Review date:</strong> scheduled pre-collection review</div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <h3>3. Reconnaissance & Site Assessment</h3>
            <p>Conduct site visit during flowering to:</p>
            <ul style="margin-left:2rem;">
                <li>Confirm species presence and population size (count plants)</li>
                <li>Assess plant health and seed crop potential (estimate % of plants with fruit)</li>
                <li>Mark up to 20 plants with GPS and biodegradable flagging tape for later return</li>
                <li>Identify access issues, hazards, sensitive areas (wetlands, nesting sites)</li>
                <li>Check for nesting birds, threatened species habitat (consult threatened species lists)</li>
                <li>Collect soil sample for pH/texture if needed for provenance matching</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>4. Work Plan Review Process</h3>
            <table class="tool-matrix">
                <tr><th>Review trigger</th><th>Action required</th><th>Documentation</th></tr>
                <tr><td>Weather changes (rain, extreme heat, fire danger)</td><td>Delay collection if rain/fire risk; adjust drying plan; postpone if total fire ban</td><td>Note on work plan revision with date</td></tr>
                <tr><td>Phenology shift (early/late ripening)</td><td>Adjust collection dates, may need new reconnaissance visit</td><td>Update collection schedule, inform supervisor</td></tr>
                <tr><td>Access issues (gate locked, road closed)</td><td>Contact landholder, find alternate site, or delay</td><td>Record in review section with photos</td></tr>
                <tr><td>Species unavailable (crop failure, fire damage)</td><td>Select alternative species meeting fruit type requirements (from approved list)</td><td>Seek supervisor approval, update species list</td></tr>
                <tr><td>Permit delay</td><td>Do not proceed until permit received; reschedule</td><td>Note permit receipt date in log</td></tr>
            </table>
        </div>

